First Character ever, paladin....60+ levels later I just finally realized I don't really enjoy being one.<br>
<br>
Second Character, Druid... 42 levels later, love this class for it's usefulness...to me.  I use my druid for all sorts of activities it would take any other character longer to accomplish.<br>
<br>
Third Character, Warrior...  52 levels later, love this guy.  Think that being a warrior is a ton of fun, but you are VERY limited in what you can do.  Basically, nothing solo.<br>
<br>
Fourth Character, Shaman, .....deleted ....arggghhhh<br>
<br>
Fifth Character,  Cleric....  level 41 now...  still like this class when I want to be lazy... and lets admit it, there is &quot;some&quot; work that goes into being a cleric, but for the most part it's &quot;CH in, SoAndSo NEXT!&quot; and then med till your turn comes back up.  <br>
<br>
Sixth Character,  Necromancer ..... level 26 ..... like this class, but got a little boring for me.<br>
<br>
Seventh CHaracter, Beastlord...  deleted ..... another Arggghhh<br>
<br>
Eighth character, Ranger... level 20....  I just liked the idea of tracking really...and druid does an okay job so this guy sits ideal.<br>
<br>
Ninth Character, Wizzie.....  deleted...... why?.......<br>
<br>
Tenth Character, Magician ...... level 29 and rising.  My new main character and the only one I play unless farming (for now).   <br>
<br>
I started this game wanting to play a Paladin, I'll be honest.  After about a week, I remember see'ing a Mage and thinking that it would be kewl but was always to scared of the pure caster.   Ya know what I mean, always dieing to the orc pawn and the like.  It was scarey back in the day.  A lowbie, level 1 or 2...starting out in a new game.  I wanted every advantage and paladins could tank and heal themselves.    <br>
<br>
After 3 years, and little success with any character, small advancements and what have you.  I finally realized (with a little twinking) that starting a Mage would be a reality and what the hell, I might as well.  Played everything else right?<br>
<br>
I am in love.  Do I hate not having root, sure.  Do I hate dying (which still happens, often I might add) sure.  But it's such a change.  It's such a rush, and it's so much fun.<br>
<br>
I don't care that Magicians may or may not be the most powerful class in the game.  What I do know is that we are in the top 5 for sure.  That Magicians do rock and roll when they need too.  <br>
<br>
I don't group much, but I was in a full group in Paludal Cavens the other day and the puller brought 6 mobs into camp.<br>
<br>
We had a chanter mezzing as best she could ( you know how these groups are at level 22 or so.  Assist is still a few levels off)  At any rate, I am assisting the main tank we set up and sending in pet and nuking like crazy.<br>
<br>
I basically solo'ed 5 of them before I ran out of mana, pet was still alive and I was at full health.  Sure, the group's melee did good being in the middle of all that and we did lose the SK cause healer was sleeping I think, but after that experience, I can't see playing anything else.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
